<TITLE> Khulna chamber chief gets bail </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Khulna, July 2 (bdnews24.com)Khulna chamber chief and BNP leader Shaharuzzaman Mortoza was granted bail Monday in a case under the Passport Act. Khulna metropolitan magistrate Golam Rahman granted the bail. Khulna Sadar police sub-inspector Jamil Hossain, the investigation officer in the case, said Shahar, president of Khulna Chamber of Commerce and Industry, was produced before Khulna Metropolitan Magistrate's Court. The police appealed for five-day remand. More than 50 lawyers, including advocate Manjur-ul-Al and advocate Sheikh Masud Hossain, then appealed to court to grant Mortoza bail. After hearing the prayer, the magistrate granted bail. Khulna Sadar police arrested Mortoza at his home in the city's Hospital Ghat area on June 29 for holding two passports. bdnews24.c
